00:07:29.246 --> 00:07:32.946 A:middle
that every language has a
code associated with it,

00:07:32.996 --> 00:07:36.086 A:middle
and of course, every region has
a code associated with it also.

00:07:36.736 --> 00:07:40.546 A:middle
So let's say a user chooses
Spanish, United States.

00:07:41.086 --> 00:07:43.946 A:middle
What that becomes at the end

00:07:43.946 --> 00:07:49.066 A:middle
of the day is a language
code like es-US.

00:07:49.206 --> 00:07:50.386 A:middle
What you may not know is

00:07:50.386 --> 00:07:53.296 A:middle
that language codes are
part of hierarchies.

00:07:53.676 --> 00:07:56.916 A:middle
So for example, Spanish,
United States actually inherits

00:07:56.916 --> 00:07:58.296 A:middle
from Latin American Spanish

00:07:58.296 --> 00:08:00.106 A:middle
which then inherits
from base Spanish.

00:07:58.296 --> 00:08:00.106 A:middle
which then inherits
from base Spanish.

00:08:00.906 --> 00:08:04.186 A:middle
This is really important
because not every app is going

00:08:04.186 --> 00:08:07.606 A:middle
to be localized into
Spanish, United States.

00:08:07.696 --> 00:08:10.666 A:middle
So we want to know, okay,
what is the next best language

00:08:10.666 --> 00:08:11.846 A:middle
that the user would prefer

00:08:11.846 --> 00:08:14.696 A:middle
if we don't have their most
preferred language available

00:08:14.786 --> 00:08:17.826 A:middle
on the system.

00:08:17.956 --> 00:08:21.856 A:middle
Also, this hierarchy is not just
for Spanish but even languages

00:08:21.856 --> 00:08:23.356 A:middle
like English have a hierarchy.

00:08:23.356 --> 00:08:27.346 A:middle
For example, Indian
English has spelling systems

00:08:27.346 --> 00:08:30.616 A:middle
that are more close
to British English

00:08:30.616 --> 00:08:33.916 A:middle
than to American English, and
so it is part of the hierarchy

00:08:33.916 --> 00:08:36.256 A:middle
in which it inherits
from British English.

00:08:36.966 --> 00:08:39.736 A:middle
And English and Spanish are
far from the only two languages

00:08:39.736 --> 00:08:41.086 A:middle
that have such a hierarchy.

00:08:41.556 --> 00:08:44.436 A:middle
We also have other languages
like Chinese, French,

00:08:44.496 --> 00:08:47.076 A:middle
and Portuguese that have
similar hierarchies.

